1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,410
It's true that many factors outside your control do affect your destination.

2
00:00:05,760 --> 00:00:11,731
There may be serious illness or death in your family, the job you're gunning for may be dissolved,

3
00:00:11,840 --> 00:00:13,731
you may meet with an accident.

4
00:00:14,240 --> 00:00:17,731
So here is a point we must fix firmly in mind.

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:21,171
Prepare to take detours in stride.

6
00:00:21,680 --> 00:00:26,530
If you are driving down a road and you come to a road closed situation,

7
00:00:26,640 --> 00:00:29,731
you wouldn't camp there nor would you go back home.

8
00:00:29,920 --> 00:00:35,171
The road closed simply means you can't go where you want to go on this road.

9
00:00:35,360 --> 00:00:38,930
You'd simply find another road to take you where you want to go.

10
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:42,370
Observe what military leaders do.

11
00:00:42,480 --> 00:00:48,611
When they develop a master plan to take an objective, they also map out alternative plans.

12
00:00:48,720 --> 00:00:57,091
If something unforeseen happens that rules out Plan A, they switch to Plan B. You rest easy in an airplane,

13
00:00:57,120 --> 00:01:08,291
even though the airport where you plan to land is closed in, because you know the fellow up there driving the plane has alternative landing fields and a reserve fuel supply.

14
00:01:08,880 --> 00:01:14,611
It's a rare person who has achieved high-level success who has not had to take detours,

15
00:01:14,720 --> 00:01:15,731
many of them.

16
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:19,970
When we detour, we don't have to change our goals.

17
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:22,691
We just travel a different route.

18
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:33,490
You've probably heard many persons say something like, oh, how I wish I had bought XX stock back in 19 blank.

19
00:01:33,601 --> 00:01:35,970
I'd have a pile of money today.

20
00:01:36,720 --> 00:01:44,211
Normally, people think of investing in terms of stocks or bonds, real estate, or some other type of property.

21
00:01:44,561 --> 00:01:53,651
But the biggest and most rewarding kind of investment is self-investment, purchasing things that build mental power and proficiency.
